Sentencas: High power density and longevity are required to commercialize solid oxide fuel cells for vehicular applications.
Titulo: Progress in durability of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells with infiltrated electrodes

Sentencas: In this work, electrochemical durability of high-performance metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells (MS-SOFCs) with infiltrated catalysts is investigated.
Titulo: Progress in durability of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells with infiltrated electrodes

Sentencas: Durability screening of various cathode and anode compositions is conducted.
Titulo: Progress in durability of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells with infiltrated electrodes

Sentencas: The Pr6O11 cathode and SDCN40 (40 vol% Ni-60 vol% SDC) anode are selected due to preferential tradeoff between performance and durability.
Titulo: Progress in durability of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells with infiltrated electrodes

Sentencas: X-ray diffraction indicates the catalyst phases are stable after prolonged thermal annealing.
Titulo: Progress in durability of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells with infiltrated electrodes

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance and scanning electron microscopy analyses show that the evolution of SDCN40 is minimal, and coarsening and Cr poisoning of the Pr6O11 catalyst are the dominant degradation mechanisms.
Titulo: Progress in durability of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells with infiltrated electrodes

Sentencas: These degradation mechanisms are addressed by implementing three additional fabrication steps: (1) preoxidation of the metal support, (2) deposition of thin and protective atomic layer deposition (ALD) coatings throughout the cathode-side electrode and support, and (3) in situ pre-coarsening of the catalysts.
Titulo: Progress in durability of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells with infiltrated electrodes

Sentencas: A favorable tradeoff is achieved: the combination of the three fabrication steps reduces degradation rate at 0.7 V and 700 degrees C by two orders of magnitude to 2.3% kh(-1), while sacrificing 35% of initial power density.
Titulo: Progress in durability of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells with infiltrated electrodes

Sentencas: The catalyst pre-coarsening step is primarily responsible for the loss of performance.
Titulo: Progress in durability of metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells with infiltrated electrodes
